{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>The Proton pump-interactor protein family (PPI, which includes PPI1-4 from Arabidopsis and BIP103/131 from rice) is implicated in the regulation of plasma membrane ATPase activity in plants. Members of this family may interact with the plasma membrane ATPases, such as AHA1, to modulate their activity [[cite:PUB00155293], [cite:PUB00070626], [cite:PUB00155363], [cite:PUB00155364]]. PPI2 is known to promote AHA1 activity by binding to a unique site, suggesting a role in the fine-tuning of ATPase function [cite:PUB00155363]]. These interactions are crucial for maintaining ion gradients across the plasma membrane, which is essential for various physiological processes including nutrient uptake, pH regulation, and cell volume control.</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR32219" "RNA-BINDING PROTEIN YLMH-RELATED"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Proton pump-interactor 1-4", "short" "PPI1-4"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 273, "taxa" 1068, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 1946, "sets" 0, "proteins" 1946, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 1063}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR055282", :literature {"PUB00155293" {"URL" nil, "issue" "4", "authors" ["Morandini P" "Valera M" "Albumi C" "Bonza MC" "Giacometti S" "Ravera G" "Murgia I" "Soave C" "De Michelis MI."], "ISO_journal" "Plant J", "DOI_URL" "https://doi.org/10.1046/j.1365-313x.2002.01373.x", "medline_journal" "Plant J", "title" "A novel interaction partner for the C-terminus of Arabidopsis thaliana plasma membrane H+-ATPase (AHA1 isoform): site and mechanism of action on H+-ATPase activity differ from those of 14-3-3 proteins.", "year" 2002, "raw_pages" "487-97", "volume" "31", "ISBN" nil, "PM